## What This Project Does
 
MindGuard analyzes your daily journal entries using NLP and Machine Learning
to detect early signs of burnout and provide personalized recovery suggestions.
 
**Flow:**
```
Write Journal → NLP Analysis → ML Prediction → Score + Reasons → Recovery Plan
```
 
---
 
## Tech Stack
 
### Frontend
| Technology | Version | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| React | 18.x | UI framework |
| Vite | 5.x | Build tool and dev server |
| Framer Motion | 11.x | Page transitions and animations |
| Three.js | 0.163.x | 3D brain orb visualization |
| @react-three/fiber | 8.x | React wrapper for Three.js |
| @react-three/drei | 9.x | Three.js helpers |
| Recharts | 2.x | Burnout and trend charts |
| Lucide React | 0.363.x | Icons |
| Axios | 1.x | HTTP requests (some pages) |
 
### Backend
| Technology | Version | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Python | 3.9+ | Backend language |
| FastAPI | 0.110.0 | REST API framework |
| Uvicorn | 0.29.0 | ASGI server |
| NLTK | 3.8.1 | NLP toolkit |
| VADER (NLTK) | built-in | Sentiment analysis |
| TextBlob | 0.18.0 | Polarity and subjectivity |
| scikit-learn | 1.4.2 | Random Forest ML model |
| NumPy | 1.26.4 | Numerical computation |
| Pandas | 2.2.1 | Data handling |
 
### Storage
| Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|
| JSON file (data_store.json) | Stores last 30 journal entries locally |
| Pickle file (burnout_model.pkl) | Stores trained ML model |
 
---
 
## Project Structure
 
```
mindguard/
├── backend/
│   ├── venv/                        # Python virtual environment
│   └── app/
│       ├── main.py                  # FastAPI app entry point
│       ├── data_store.json          # Entry history storage
│       ├── routers/
│       │   ├── __init__.py
│       │   └── analyze.py           # API endpoints
│       └── services/
│           ├── __init__.py
│           ├── nlp_engine.py        # NLP pipeline (preprocessing + emotion + patterns)
│           ├── ml_predictor.py      # Random Forest model + prediction
│           ├── recommender.py       # Dynamic recommendations + recovery plan
│           └── burnout_model.pkl    # Saved trained model (auto-generated)
│
└── frontend/
    ├── src/
    │   ├── App.jsx                  # Main app + routing
    │   ├── index.css                # Global styles
    │   ├── main.jsx                 # React entry point
    │   ├── pages/
    │   │   ├── LandingPage.jsx      # Home page
    │   │   ├── JournalPage.jsx      # Journal input form
    │   │   ├── Dashboard.jsx        # Results + score display
    │   │   ├── InsightsPage.jsx     # Trend charts
    │   │   └── RecoveryPage.jsx     # Daily recovery plan
    │   └── components/
    │       ├── Navbar.jsx           # Navigation bar
    │       └── BrainOrb.jsx         # 3D animated sphere
    ├── vite.config.js               # Vite config with proxy
    └── package.json
```
 
---
 
## How to Run — Step by Step
 
### Prerequisites
- Python 3.9 or higher
- Node.js 18 or higher
- npm
 
### Step 1 — Set Up Backend
 
```powershell
# Open Terminal 1
cd mindguard/backend
 
# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
 
# Activate (Windows)
venv\Scripts\activate
 
# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
 
# Download NLTK data (run once only)
python -c "import nltk; nltk.download('vader_lexicon'); nltk.download('stopwords'); nltk.download('punkt')"
```
 
### Step 2 — Start Backend
 
```powershell
# Still in mindguard/backend with venv active
uvicorn app.main:app --reload 

 
### Step 3 — Set Up Frontend
 
```powershell
# Open Terminal 2
cd mindguard/frontend
npm install
```
 
### Step 4 — Start Frontend
 
```powershell
npm run dev
```